      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 177: The dedupe key is built by concatenating unescaped payload fields with \u0027:\u0027. Because both \u0027to\u0027 and \u0027key\u0027 come from the remote payload and may contain the delimiter, different tuples can collapse to the same string and incorrectly suppress a genuine incoming call. Use a structured key instead of string concatenation.\n\n```suggestion\n        val scope \u003d CallValueScope(\n            remoteMessage.data[\"to\"].orEmpty(),\n            remoteMessage.data[\"key\"].orEmpty()\n        )\n```\nThen store a data-class key, for example `private data class SeenCallId(val to: String, val key: String, val id: String)`, and call `seenCallIds.put(SeenCallId(scope.to, scope.key, id), Unit)`.",
